mor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152019/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-7-297x210.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152019/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-7-800x566.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152019/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-7-120x85.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152019/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-7-768x543.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152019/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-7-1536x1086.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>The one-off frame includes a number of machined parts including the dropouts and inserts for the steerer tube clamps at the head tube.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12.jpg\" alt=\"Loris Klin bikepacking bags\" width=\"2246\" height=\"1519\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12.jpg 2246w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-297x201.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-800x541.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-768x519.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-1536x1039.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-2048x1385.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2246px) 100vw, 2246px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12.jpg 2246w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-297x201.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-800x541.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-768x519.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-1536x1039.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152035/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-12-2048x1385.jpg 2048w\"></a></p><p>Then, there are the bags themselves. Opting for a hard shell bag design instead of soft, the rigid containers are made from flax fiber and are easily installed or removed. The design does require an extra long seat tube, so dropper posts will not be an option here, but you can’t really use a dropper if you’re running a big saddle bag anyway. The main container is 6L and features two side openings with stretched canvas ‘doors’. Loris states that hard bags allow for you to compact the contents without the bags ‘bowing’ out, and it allows things to be packed tight to avoid rattling.</p><p>The front two bags are made in a similar style with smaller capacities. One of the requirements for the competition was to carry 4L of water, so there is room for 1L in the main bag, and Loris added a Camelbak with a 3L capacity to make up the rest. But with all the room left in the front triangle, it seems water bottle mounts could be added as well.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9.jpg\" alt=\"Loris Klin front end\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/14152025/Loris-Klin-bikepacking-concept-bike-handmade-Concourse-de-Machines-9-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Total weight? The bike itself is said to be 11.8kg (26.01lb). With all the equipment (includes tent, sleeping kit, cook kit, but excluding food and water), the weight is claimed to be 16.9kg (37.26lbs).</p><p>No word if Loris has any plans for offereing the Klin for sale. As it stands, it looks like their <a href=\"http://www.lorisfibre.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">website</a> is down, but you can find them on<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LORISfibrecycliste\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> facebook</a>.</p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f0fa8053dfd221e7fc727a1d80824cc0af301546c742a1d2e6ec89c5a25eecee","category":"Cycling"}